{{Hatnote|Not to be confused with [[Sapugaskanda Power Station]] and [[Lakdhanavi Power Station]].}} {{Infobox power station | name = Asia Power Sapugaskanda Power Station | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Sri Lanka | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|06|57|22|N|79|56|54|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Sri Lanka | location = [[Sapugaskanda]] | status = Operational | construction_began = 1996 | commissioned = June 1998 | decommissioned = <!-- June 2018 --> | cost = | owner = {{Nowrap|Asia Power (Pvt) Ltd}} | operator = | th_fuel_primary = [[Fuel oil]] | th_fuel_secondary = | th_fuel_tertiary = | th_technology = | th_feed_mine = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | th_cooling_source = | ps_units_operational = 8 × 6.4 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_units_manu_model = [[Deutz AG|Deutz]] 16V BVM 640 | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_thermal_capacity = | ps_electrical_capacity = 51 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_storage_hours = | ps_annual_generation = | website = | extra = PUCSL License: EL/GI/14-10<ref>{{cite web|title=Electricity Generation, Transmission and Distribution Licenses|url=http://www.pucsl.gov.lk/english/wp-content/themes/pucsl/pdfs/Licensee-List.pdf|publisher=[[Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka|PUCSL]]|accessdate=7 November 2015|format=PDF|date=1 October 2015}}</ref> }}
The '''Asia Power Sapugaskanda Power Station''' (also sometimes referred to as '''Asia Power Station''') is a {{Nowrap|51 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} thermal [[power station]] in [[Sapugaskanda]], [[Sri Lanka]]. Planning for the [[fuel oil]]-run power station dated back to 1994, when the [[Ceylon Electricity Board]] issued a tender for an [[Independent Power Producer|IPP]] project for 50 megawatts. Construction of the plant began in 1996 and was commissioned in June 1998, with a [[Power purchase agreement|PPA]] of 20-years. The power station utilizes eight {{Nowrap|[[Deutz AG|Deutz]] 16V BVM 640}} generating units.<ref name=BWSC>{{cite web|title=Sapugaskanda Power Plant|url=http://www.bwsc.com/Sapugaskanda-Power-Plant--Sri-Lanka.aspx?ID=214|publisher=BWSC.com|accessdate=7 November 2015}}</ref> {{Clear}}
