'''Solar Splash''' is an intercollegiate solar/[[electric boat]] competition dedicated to showing the feasibility of [[solar energy]].<ref>[http://www.ieee-pels.org/education/competitions/solar-splash Solar Splash], [[IEEE Power Electronics Society]]</ref>

An annual collegiate [[Electric boat#Types|solar boating]] competition started in 1994. The 2007 contest was hosted by the City of [[Fayetteville, Arkansas]], and the [[University of Arkansas]] College of Engineering. It took place June 13–17.

